      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to go past the former Victorian SELF SERVE (1) who makes debut for the new yard. Formerly with the Danny O'Brien yard, the lightly raced mare goes well fresh and is expected to hit the ground running for the new team. GOOD ONYA DARL (8) turned in a nice run fresh and looks the main threat. Was runner-up behind Southampton Flare last time, who is in the previous race. Fitter for the run and will take catching. SASSY ABBEY (5) is going well and should be in the finish. Placed 2/3 this course and distance and looks a leading chance. STARSPANGLEDANCER (6) was safely held fresh but fitter for that run and expected to be in the finish this time. JUELENE (4) was well below best last time and rates highly on previous form.",
